<h1 class="hero-h">The AI Tool Stack for a 30-Person Company <em style="color:#00C853;font-style:italic;">Less than you think.</em></h1>
<p class="hero-sub">A common question from CEOs of 20-50 person B2B companies in 2026: what AI tools do we actually need? This is the honest answer — short list, clear reasoning, no kickbacks. Most companies overspend on AI tooling by 3-5x.</p>
<div class="tldr"><div class="tldr-l">Short answer</div><p class="tldr-p">One LLM platform (Claude Team or ChatGPT Team) + your existing CRM and email + a meeting transcription tool. Total monthly cost ~$1,200-$2,500 for a 30-person team. Everything else is usually a wrap or duplication.</p></div>
</div></div>

<div style="background:#0A1A0A;border-top:1px solid #1A3A1A;border-bottom:1px solid #1A3A1A;padding:1.25rem 2.5rem;">
<div style="max-width:880px;margin:0 auto;display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center;gap:1rem;flex-wrap:wrap;font-size:0.78rem;color:#8FAF8F;">
<div>By <a href="/about" style="color:#F0FFF0;text-decoration:none;font-weight:500;">Bill Colbert</a> · <span style="color:#4A6A4A;">Founder, Treetop Growth Strategy</span></div>
<div style="color:#4A6A4A;">Published May 2026 · <a href="/content-library" style="color:#8FAF8F;text-decoration:none;">More from the library</a></div>
</div>
</div>

<section><div class="sec-inner"><h2 class="h2">The recommended stack</h2><ol class="ol"><li><strong>Claude Team or ChatGPT Team</strong> — \$30/user/month. Seats for everyone in workflows that benefit, not just leadership.</li><li><strong>Your existing CRM</strong> (HubSpot, Salesforce, Pipedrive) with whatever AI features it has — already paid for.</li><li><strong>Your existing email/calendar</strong> (Google Workspace or Microsoft 365) with built-in AI — already paid for.</li><li><strong>One meeting transcription tool</strong> (Fathom, Otter, Granola, or Gong if you have it) — \$15-\$40/user/month.</li><li><strong>That's the stack.</strong> Total monthly for 30 people: roughly \$1,200-\$2,500.</li></ol></div></section>
<section><div class="sec-inner"><h2 class="h2">What you don't need (yet)</h2><ul class="ul"><li><strong>AI SDR tools.</strong> Outbound AI agents perform poorly in 2026 (see <a href="/state-of-ai-in-b2b-sales-2026" style="color:#00C853;">state of B2B sales</a>).</li><li><strong>AI content marketing platforms.</strong> Claude/ChatGPT does this for you.</li><li><strong>AI customer service platforms beyond your existing helpdesk.</strong> Use AI features in Gorgias/Front/Zendesk.</li><li><strong>AI sales coaching tools.</strong> Mature products are expensive (\$50-\$100/user/month) and adoption is hard; usually not worth it at this size.</li><li><strong>AI proposal/RFP platforms.</strong> Claude Project + your past proposals does the same thing for free.</li><li><strong>Multiple LLM platforms.</strong> Pick one. Add the second later if needed.</li></ul></div></section>
<section><div class="sec-inner"><h2 class="h2">What might be worth adding by 50 people</h2><ul class="ul"><li>Conversation intelligence (Gong, Chorus) if sales motion is heavy.</li><li>Customer success platform with AI (Vitally, Catalyst) if you have a CS team.</li><li>Marketing automation with strong AI (HubSpot/Marketo enhanced) if marketing is the growth engine.</li><li>Specialized vertical tool if you operate in a vertical where the AI integration is genuinely differentiated.</li></ul></div></section>
<section><div class="sec-inner"><h2 class="h2">Total cost benchmarks</h2></div></section>

<section><div class="sec-inner"><h2 class="h2">FAQ</h2>
<div class="faq-q"><h3 class="faq-qh">Should I pick Claude or ChatGPT?</h3><p class="faq-qa">Default to Claude for most B2B workflows; ChatGPT if Microsoft-heavy. See <a href="/claude-vs-chatgpt-2026" style="color:#00C853;">our 2026 comparison</a>.</p></div>
<div class="faq-q"><h3 class="faq-qh">Do I need both Team-tier AI and individual Pro subscriptions?</h3><p class="faq-qa">No. Team tier covers what Pro covers for business workflows. Consolidate.</p></div>
<div class="faq-q"><h3 class="faq-qh">Do I need a vector database or RAG system?</h3><p class="faq-qa">No, at 30 people, almost certainly not. Claude Projects with loaded knowledge handles your knowledge needs.</p></div>
<div class="faq-q"><h3 class="faq-qh">What about agents and orchestration tools?</h3><p class="faq-qa">Skip. At this size, you do not need orchestration. Build workflows in Projects.</p></div>
<div class="faq-q"><h3 class="faq-qh">Should I buy AI tools from my existing vendors?</h3><p class="faq-qa">Often yes — your CRM and email already include AI features. Use what you have before buying more.</p></div>
</div></section>

